2011-04-12T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/banco-espanol-de-credito-ferrovial-iberian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain ’s IBEX 35 Index declined 0.3 percent to 10,878.30.
Portugal’s PSI-20 Index added 0.1 percent to 7,916.32.  Spanish stocks:  Banco Espanol de Credito SA (BTO)  : The unit of Banco
Santander SA (SAN SM) is scheduled to publish its first-quarter
earnings before trading starts. Banesto shares declined 0.2
percent to 6.68 euros.  Ferrovial SA (FER)  : Spain’s second-largest builder by
market capitalization plans to borrow about $2.5 billion in
euros and pounds to refinance debt, according to three people
with knowledge of the situation. The stock retreated 1.3 percent
to 9.17 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
